    "### Fit, Good Fit, Underfit & Overfit (Intuition)\n",
    "\n",
    "* **Good fit (Intuition):** Refers to a model that accurately captures the underlying patterns in the data while avoiding overfitting and underfitting. \n",
    "* **Underfitting:** Occurs when a model is too simple and fails to learn the relevant patterns in the data (high bias).\n",
    "* **Overfitting:** Happens when a model learns the training data *too* well, including random noise and outliers, and performs poorly on new, unseen data (high variance)."
   ]
